// @check
// @error expected an expression but found COMMA
// @error expected RBRACK but found NUMBER
// @error expected an expression but found RBRACK
// A doubled comma in an array literal (`[1,,2]`) is still a syntax error: only a
// single trailing comma before `]` is allowed, never an empty slot. The doubled
// comma derails the literal, so the recovery cascade is declared in full.
let a = [1,, 2]
